Get the IPv4 address one line for Linux:

ip -4 -o addr show ens160 | awk '{print $4}'

Output is : 10.50.4.78/20

ip -4 -o addr show ens160 | awk '{print $4}' | sed 's/\/20//g'

Output:
  10.50.4.78


